article_title: Private Insurers Net 9.3 Million From ACA's Medicaid Expansion

article_metadata.author: Bruce Japsen

og.description: New customers from the expansion of Medicaid benefits for poor Americans under the Affordable Care Act helped private managed care plans increase enrollment by 9.3 million people, according to a new report. Managed-care plans are taking on a greater role even in states that didn’t go along with the Medicaid expansion. [...]
